The paper deals with the problem of exploring text networks, which involves analyzing the relationships between documents represented by edges. This falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed model is a probabilistic generative model, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.DL) and probabilistic graphical models (cs.LG). The prototype demo system named TopicAtlas involves web development and user interface design, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
